goals.question: How do the 'normal' values vary by 'day'?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify any patterns or trends in the 'normal' values by 'day' and understand how they vary over time.

code:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    normal_values = data['normal']
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.hist(normal_values, bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    ax.axvline(normal_values.mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {normal_values.mean():.2f}")
    ax.axvline(normal_values.median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {normal_values.median():.2f}")
    ax.legend()
    plt.title("What is the distribution of 'normal' values in the dataset?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.sort_values(by='day')
    plt.plot(data['day'], data['actual'], label='Actual')
    plt.plot(data['day'], data['forecast'], label='Forecast')
    plt.legend()

    return plt

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    plt.scatter(data['normal'], data['actual'])

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['difference'] = pd.to_numeric(data['difference'], errors='coerce')
    plt.hist(data['difference'], bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['difference'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['difference'].median()))
    plt.title("What is the distribution of 'difference' values in the dataset?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.boxplot(data['normal'].groupby(data['day'].dt.day).apply(list), showfliers=False)
    ax.set_xlabel('Day of the Month')
    ax.set_ylabel('Normal Values')
    ax.set_title("How do the 'normal' values vary by 'day'?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
